<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3667] SQL roles: Make CURRENT_ROLE check that the role is still valid</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3667</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a role is the current role of a session, and that role is either&lt;br/&gt;
a) revoked from current user or dropped, the present implementation&lt;br/&gt;
does not actually reset the current role of value of the session which&lt;br/&gt;
has set it to current, but instead lazily relies on the next usage to&lt;br/&gt;
discover this fact by validating that the role usage is still&lt;br/&gt;
applicable. This check is missing from CURRENT_USER.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12395511">DERBY-3667</key>
            <summary>SQL roles: Make CURRENT_ROLE check that the role is still valid</summary>
